Program: Outlook
Title: 19/07/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00hvffz
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 20 Jul 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Anwar Khokhar, the Pakistani barber who reunites missing children and their parents. Also, Susan Phoenix, the British woman who lost her husband in a military helicopter crash 17 years ago - on news that the government has finally exonerated the pilots. And Renato Hausler, the Swiss nightwatchman who calls the time from the cathedral belfry in Lausanne. Show less